        <description>&lt;img src="https://hyruo.com/article/updating-to-vivo-smartphone-and-watch/images/img_20240401_0932495013864575354211093.jpg" alt="Featured image of post Updating to VIVO Smartphone and Watch" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recently, I purchased the Vivo X100 Pro smartphone and also got the Vivo Watch 3 smartwatch. Additionally, because I found my previous mobile plan with China Mobile to be too expensive, I added a mobile SIM card plan from China Broadcasting Network. Here, I&amp;rsquo;ll briefly share my experiences with these products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;vivo-x100-pro&#34;&gt;VIVO X100 PRO
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Vivo X100 Pro claims to be one of the most powerful camera phones among domestic Chinese smartphones. From my recent usage, I feel it lives up to this reputation, and I decisively chose the 1TB storage version when purchasing. The Dimensity 9300 CPU it&amp;rsquo;s equipped with is a significant upgrade from the Dimensity 9000 in the Vivo X80 I used previously, and the memory has also increased from 12GB to 16GB, which means I probably won&amp;rsquo;t need to consider changing phones for a few years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before using the Vivo X80, I had never purchased any Vivo products, nor had I bought anything from its sister brand, OPPO. However, in the past few years, Vivo and OPPO have frequently been among the top five in China&amp;rsquo;s smartphone sales rankings, and sometimes even in the top five globally. During the period when Huawei was unreasonably sanctioned by the U.S. government and couldn&amp;rsquo;t produce 5G phones, I was due for a phone upgrade and bought the Vivo X80, my first 5G phone. I was immediately impressed. Whether it&amp;rsquo;s the phone&amp;rsquo;s system features, smooth operation, or camera performance, this phone has brought me great surprises. In my history of using BlackBerry, iPhone, Samsung, and Huawei phones, I believe this product ranks in the top three in my mind, along with the BlackBerry 9780 and iPhone 4s.&lt;/p&gt;
